// Companion to test_bare_return_main: `return <value>` from an untyped main
// must keep compiling (main is emitted as `long long wyn_main()` and the value
// becomes the process exit status). The runner only checks stdout, so behavior
// is encoded via prints before/after the return. (2026-07)
fn main() {
    println("before")
    if 1 == 1 {
        println("returning")
        return 2
    }
    println("unreached")
}
// EXPECT: before
// EXPECT: returning
